Visual Studio Code and Anaconda Installation Tutorial¶

  • Visual Studio Code (aka. VS code) is a code editor redefined and optimized for building and debugging modern web and cloud applications.
  • Anaconda is a useful tool for python environment management

1. Anaconda installation¶

You can either install Anaconda or Miniconda, however for this tutorial, I'll show you how to install miniconda

1.1 Download miniconda¶

Download miniconda via this site or use this link(exe) to get 64-bit the exe

1.2 Keep pressing next or I agree until this page show up, make sure to check register Miniconda3 as my default Python 3.8¶

1.3 Wait for the installation to complete¶

1.4 Press start and type Anaconda Powershell prompt¶

1.5 create this subject environment using the following command¶

conda create -n comprog_enc python=3.8 -y

1.6 activate the environment¶

conda activate comprog_enc

1.7 install pygame library¶

pip install pygame

Anaconda installation is completed¶

2. Visual Studio Code (aka. VS code) Installation¶

2.1. Download installer from the web site or click the links below¶

  • Windows
  • Linux
  • Mac

2.2. open installer¶

2.3. Accep the agrement and next¶

2.4 Next while keeping every other option check¶

2.5 repeat next and wait for installation to finish then open VS code¶

2.6 select extension page then type python then press install (mine is already install)¶

2.7 Also install Anaconda extension pack¶

2.8 Click File>New File¶

2.9 save the file as python hello.py¶

2.10 type in¶

print("Hello Comprog")

2.11 Save File>Save or Ctrl + S¶

2.12 change environment to comprog_enc¶

2.13 Running in terminal by right click > Run Python File in Terminal¶

2.14 make sure you see Hello ComProg show up in the terminal¶

2.15 Test library Pygame¶

2.16 First download and extract this file¶

2.17 Open that folder up in VS code File > Open Folder¶

2.18 Open setting using Ctrl + Shift + P type Open Settings (json)¶

2.19 add the following to the setting then save¶

{
    "[python]": {
        "editor.defaultFormatter": "ms-python.python",
        "editor.formatOnSave": true
    },
    "python.formatting.provider": "autopep8",
    "python.formatting.autopep8Args": [
        "--max-line-length=150",
    ],
    "python.linting.pylintEnabled": true,
    "python.linting.pylintArgs": ["--generate-members"]
}

2.20 back to the file test_pygame.py right click > Run Python FIle in Terminal and you should get this window show up¶
